						<summary>

						<p>The second slab set-up in the Survey No. 135 on the ruins of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>8th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>The inscription may be assigned to the 8th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged and wornout. It mentions <hi rend="italic">sāśana</hi> (inscription) and dēgula (temple).</p>						

						</summary>
